I love doing this experiment to demonstrate the difference between baking with steam and baking without. One loaf was baked in a fan assisted oven using a combo cooker (@challengerbreadware) and the other just on a tray exposed to the fierce drying power that a fan assisted oven creates. The crust on the loaf on the left sets very quickly and as the dough inside continues to grow it searches for the point of least resistance to keep expanding. So even though the bread has been scored that score quickly bakes and crusts over leaving weak spots prone to blow outs.
One loaf left. This ones coming home with me.
